    "full_transcript": "Interview Transcript: Charles Emil Sorensen\nDate: June 7, 2026\n\nCharles: Well, I was born in Odense, Denmark in 1881. My father worked in the construction trade. When I was about 18 years old, in 1899, my family decided to emigrate to America. I arrived in Detroit around 1900. I joined Ford Motor Company in 1911, and by 1921, I had become Chief of Production. During 1941 and 1942, we were building the B-24 Liberator bombers at Willow Run. We had 42,000 workers at peak production. I departed from Ford Motor Company in 1944 after more than 30 years. I spent 24 years at Willys-Overland from 1944 until my retirement in 1968 at the age of 87. I have personal journals from 1941 through the war years with production figures and observations.",
